      <hedline>
        <hl1>GUCCI BENEFITS FROM LUXURY DEMAND</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By John Tagliabue</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Tagliabue, John</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gucci Group revenue rises in second quarter to $497 million from $261 million a year ago; net profit rises 6 percent, to $80.9 million, largely because of restructuring costs (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Lifted by recent acquisitions and strong sales of its luxury leather goods, the Gucci Group reported that revenue almost doubled in the second quarter, to $497 million, from $261 million in the period a year earlier. But net profit rose only 6 percent, to $80.9 million, largely because of restructuring costs.</p>
        <p>John Tagliabue (NYT)</p>
      </block>
